<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1414,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet, to be treated as a noun in apposition, is a word used in 
<collectingCountry box="[1098,1166,1414,1439]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Brazil</collectingCountry>
for black water flooded forest in the Amazon, since the specimens reported here were collected from that habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1486,1511]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species can be recognized by having the embolus with no abrupt angle (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1360,1486,1511]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the embolus extends straight distally and then forms an angle at its middle; see 
<figureCitation box="[1137,1218,1522,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Also, males of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. igapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[222,312,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[222,312,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
have larger terminal apophysis and smaller RTA (
<figureCitation box="[876,960,1558,1583]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1206,1559,1582]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1111,1206,1559,1582]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. igapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1213,1303,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1213,1303,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
have round copulatory openings, the spermathecae are larger and the dorsal coupling pocket is not centralized, almost paired (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1630,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Figs 43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[257,332,1631,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">48–49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,556,1666,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus box="[434,543,1666,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 5.91. Although the specimen is not perfectly preserved, color pattern as described for the genus (
<figureCitation box="[538,622,1702,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Carapace 3.07 long, 2.23 wide, 1.69 high. Ocular quadrangle 1.77 long. Anterior eye row 2.23 wide and posterior 2.00 wide. Palp as described for the genus (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1282,1738,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1297,1371,1739,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">44–47</figureCitation>
). Leg formula: 3412. Length of femur: I 1.78, II 1.70, III 2.18, IV 1.92; patella + tibia: I 2.30, II 2.06, III 2.16, IV 2.02; metatarsus + tarsus: I 1.58, II 1.61, III 2.09, IV 2.23. Leg macrosetae: femur I d1-1-1, p2di, r0; II d1-1-1, p2di, r0- 1-2; III d1-1-1, p0-1-2, r1di; IV d1-1-1, p1di, r1di; patella I=II p1, r0; III=IV p1, r1; tibia I p1-1-1, r0, 
<date box="[1318,1368,1847,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v2-1</date>
r-2; II p1-2-1, r0, 
<date box="[280,329,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v2-1</date>
r-2; III=IV p1-1-1, r2-1-1, 
<date box="[637,663,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v1</date>
p-0-2; metatarsus I=II 
